# Utility Functions

The ignite-cli uses the following utility modules:

- [logger.sh](mdc:src/utils/logger.sh): Functions for logging messages at different levels
- [validators.sh](mdc:src/utils/validators.sh): Input validation functions
- [config.sh](mdc:src/utils/config.sh): Configuration management functions
- [git.sh](mdc:src/utils/git.sh): Git operations helper functions
- [shell.sh](mdc:src/utils/shell.sh): Shell command execution utilities
- [prompts.sh](mdc:src/utils/prompts.sh): User interaction and prompt functions

These utility functions are sourced in the main script and used throughout the codebase.
